                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/989.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Premier and the Minister of Finance were informed this afternoon by the six
                    ministers of the instructions received from their several Governments. The reply
                    was that the acceptance of the terms of supervision were impossible; that the
                    National Council will not approve and public opinion will not permit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
